  "prompt": "How can I record video with Drift Ghost-S while charging?",
  "response": "To record video with the Drift Ghost-S while charging, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Connect the Charger**: Use the USB cable provided with your Drift Ghost-S to connect the camera to a power source. You can use a wall adapter or a portable power bank.\n\n2. **Power On the Camera**: Turn on the Drift Ghost-S by pressing and holding the power button until the camera boots up.\n\n3. **Start Recording**: Press the record button (usually marked with a red dot) to start recording video. You should see a red light indicator to confirm that the camera is recording.\n\n4. **Check Battery and Recording Status**: Make sure to monitor the battery level and recording status on the camera's display or through the Drift app if you have it connected to your smartphone.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to record video while the camera is charging. This is particularly useful for long recording sessions where you need to ensure the camera stays powered.",
